Diagram 3 (Resistance)
[{\rtf1\fbidis\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\ltrpar\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White's placement at 1 is the 2-1 point and it is usually a strong attack.
\par However, black's resistence at 2 works.
\par
\par \pard\ltrpar\nowidctlpar\qj Now a pae is the best result. Instead of 3, if white thoughtlessly cuts at \b\f1 A\b0\f0 , black plays at 3 and lives unconditionally.
\par }
